# agent-os schema (Windsurf)

This project uses the agent-os pattern. The root AGENTS.md is a thin stub — the canonical schema is in agent/AGENTS.md, read that first.

At session start, read in order:
1. agent/AGENTS.md — full schema (memory protocol, agent dispatch, rules table)
2. agent/memory/STATE.md — current priorities and blockers
3. agent/memory/learnings.md MISTAKES section — past corrections to avoid

On demand, based on task:
- agent/memory/wiki/INDEX.md → relevant wiki pages
- agent/memory/clients/*.md for client work
- agent/rules/<rule>.md when behavior is in question
- agent/skills/<skill>/SKILL.md when invoking a workflow

Memory protocol is Karpathy's LLM wiki pattern (3 layers: raw / wiki / outputs) extended with operational state (STATE, clients, daily, learnings) and agent state (4-file pattern per domain agent).

When in doubt about how to behave: agent/AGENTS.md is the source of truth. Do not duplicate its content here.
